you can still apply for a decree nisi. However, you&rsquo;ll have to go to a hearing at the court to discuss the case, where a judge will decide whether to grant you a decree nisi.</p>\n\n<h2>Fill in application form</h2>\n\n<p>To get a decree nisi, fill in the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=154\" title=\"application for a decree nisi\">application for a decree nisi.</a></p>\n\n<p>If your husband or wife is defending the case, fill in section B of the form, saying you want a &lsquo;case management hearing&rsquo; before the judge.</p>\n\n<p>You must also fill in a statement confirming that what you said in your divorce petition is true.</p>\n\n<p>There are 5 statement forms - use the one that covers the grounds you&rsquo;ve given for your divorce:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=142\" title=\"adultery statement\">adultery statement</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=144\" title=\"unreasonable behaviour statement\">unreasonable behaviour statement</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=146\" title=\"desertion statement\">desertion statement</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=149\" title=\"2 years' separation statement\">2 years&rsquo; separation statement</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=150\" title=\"5 years' separation statement\">5 years&rsquo; separation statement</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Attach a copy of your husband or wife&rsquo;s response to the divorce petition.</p>\n\n<h2>Getting a decree nisi</h2>\n\n<p>If the judge agrees, the court will send you and your husband or wife:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a certificate of 