ol.html\" title=\"divorce and separation calculator\">divorce and separation calculator</a> to work out your finances and what you own.</p>\n\n<p>Once you&rsquo;ve reached an agreement, you can get the court to make it legally-binding, by applying for a &lsquo;consent order&rsquo;.</p>\n\n<h2>If you can&rsquo;t agree</h2>\n\n<p>If you can&rsquo;t agree, you can ask the court to decide using a &lsquo;financial order&rsquo;.</p>\n\n<p>If you want to do this, you first have to go to a &lsquo;mediation information and assessment meeting&rsquo; with a family mediator.</p>\n\n<p>This is to find out if you can reach an agreement with your partner without going to court.</p>\n\n<p>Contact a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.familymediationhelpline.co.uk/find-service.php/\" title=\"family mediation service\">family mediation service</a> to arrange to go to a meeting.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/money-property-when-relationship-ends/apply-for-consent-order","slug":"apply-for-consent-order","order":2,"title":"Apply for a consent order","body":"<p>If you want to make an agreement legally binding, you need to get a solicitor to draft a &lsquo;consent order&rsquo;.</p>\n\n<p>This is a legal document that confirms your agreement, and can include details on how you are going to divide up your assets, including:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>money</li>\n  <li>property</li>\n  <li>savings</li>\n  <li>investments</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>It can also include arrangements for maintenance payments, including child maintenance.</p>\n\n<p>You and your ex-partner both have to sign the draft consent order.</p>\n\n<p>Both of you also need to fill in:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=2655\" title=\"notice of an application for a financial order\">notice of an application for a financial order</a></li>\n  <li>a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://hmctsformfinder.justice.gov.uk/HMCTS/GetForm.do?court_forms_id=1116\" 